article.description: Jamaal King scored 23 points, Isaiah Blackmon calmly sank two free throws -- neither time did the ball touch the rim -- with 2.8 seconds on the clock and Saint Francis (Pa.) knocked off Northeast Conference leader Robert Morris 76-73 Thursday night.
article.headline: Red Flash topple Northeast leader Robert Morris 76-73
article.linkText: Red Flash topple Northeast leader Robert Morris 76-73
article.story: MOON TOWNSHIP, Pa. -- Jamaal King scored 23 points, Isaiah Blackmon calmly sank two free throws -- neither time did the ball touch the rim -- with 2.8 seconds on the clock and Saint Francis (Pa.) knocked off Northeast Conference leader Robert Morris 76-73 Thursday night. Blackmon finished with 20 points, Keith Braxton added 19 and Saint Francis' top three scorers combined for 62. Mark Flagg scored three of his five points in the last four minutes, and pulled down three of his team-leading seven rebounds in the same span. The Red Flash (9-11, 5-4) held RMU to 1-of-3 shooting -- and 3-of-7 at the line -- in the closing minutes. Matty McConnell scored 24 points, making four 3-pointers and hauling in eight boards to pace Robert Morris (12-10, 7-2), which lost a four-game win streak but finished the month of January 7-2. Malik Petteway added 13 points and Josh Williams 10 for RMU, which shot 44 percent (24 of 54) and made just 8 of 23 shots from behind the arc. The Colonials had led by as many as 14 and for most of the first half before Saint Francis surged to a 41-39 halftime lead and stretched that by starting the second half on an 8-1 push.
